\c 8
\p
\v 1 Moreover, brethren, we do you to wit of the grace of God bestowed on the
churches of Macedonia; 
\v 2 How that in a great trial of affliction the abundance of their joy and
their deep poverty abounded unto the riches of their liberality. 
\v 3 For to \add their\add* power, I bear record, yea, and beyond \add their
\add* power \add they were\add* willing of themselves; 
\v 4 Praying us with much intreaty that we would receive the gift, and 
\add take upon us\add* the fellowship of the ministering to the saints. 
\v 5 And \add this they did,\add* not as we hoped, but first gave their own
selves to the Lord, and unto us by the will of God. 
\v 6 Insomuch that we desired Titus, that as he had begun, so he would also
finish in you the same grace also. 
\v 7 Therefore, as ye abound in every \add thing, in\add* faith, and
utterance, and knowledge, and \add in\add* all diligence, and \add in
\add* your love to us, \add see\add* that ye abound in this grace also. 
\v 8 I speak not by commandment, but by occasion of the forwardness of others,
and to prove the sincerity of your love. 
\v 9 For ye know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that, though he was rich,
