\v 11 Now therefore perform the doing \add of it;\add* that as \add there was
\add* a readiness to will, so \add there may be\add* a performance also out of
that which ye have. 
\v 12 For if there be first a willing mind, \add it is\add* accepted according
to that a man hath, \add and\add* not according to that he hath not. 
\v 13 For \add I mean\add* not that other men be eased, and ye burdened: 
\v 14 But by an equality, \add that\add* now at this time your abundance 
\add may be a supply\add* for their want, that their abundance also may be 
\add a supply\add* for your want: that there may be equality: 
\v 15 As it is written, He that \add had gathered\add* much had nothing over;
